Q1.Show the number of employees in each department.
Use COUNT(*) and GROUP BY.

SELECT Department, COUNT(Name) AS EmployeeCount
FROM Employees
GROUP BY Department

Q2.Show the average salary for each department.
Use AVG() and GROUP BY.

SELECT Department, AVG(Salary) AS AverageSalary
FROM Employees
GROUP BY Department;

Q3.Show the highest salary in each department.
Use MAX() and GROUP BY.

SELECT Department, MAX(Salary) AS HighestSalary
FROM Employees
GROUP BY Department;

Q4.Find departments where:
Total salary is greater than 80000
Use:GROUP BY, SUM, HAVING.

SELECT Department
FROM Employees
GROUP BY Department
HAVING SUM(Salary) > 80000;
